Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Leased to CBA, tenant of 36 years
Corner location of Coogee's retail strip

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 199 Coogee Bay Road, Coogee. This property Is a two storey retail freehold building occupying a prominent corner position on Coogee Bay Road and Brook Street. 199 Coogee Bay Road offers a generous 407sqm* land offering just 250m* from the renowned Coogee Beach. Positioned on the corner of Coogee’s main thoroughfare, the property benefits from a high level of exposure through its large volume of foot and vehicular traffic. The North-East aspect of 199 Coogee Bay Road allows the property to benefit from an abundance of natural light and ventilation in a location where it will never be built out.

The property offers a secure investment, underpinned by a lease to The Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA), who has occupied the building for the past 36 years. A new 3 year lease with fixed increases has commenced, with all of the outgoings being paid by the tenant. With B2 Local Centre zoning and a 12m height limit governing the site, the property also benefits from future development upside (STCA). 

The property benefit from the following key attributes:
- Brand new triple net lease to tenant of 36 years, The Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA)
- Net Income $409,450*
- Tenant pays all outgoings including land tax, water rates, council rates and property management fees
- Fixed annual increases
- GFA 585.5sqm* split across two storeys
- 250m* from Coogee Beach
- High exposure corner position benefiting from high foot and vehicular traffic
- B2 Local Centre zoning and 12m height limit, allowing for future development potential (STCA)

199 Coogee Bay Road, Coogee will sold via Public Auction on Tuesday, 25th of May 2021 at 10.30am at AuctionWORKS (live stream & online bidding available).

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent is pleased to present 218 Coogee Bay Road, Coogee. Being offered to the market for the first time in 47 years, the property is a two-storey mixed use commercial freehold building comprising two car spaces, basement storage, and rear lane access. Currently improved as a medical facility, the property includes a large reception and waiting area, generously sized office spaces, and operation rooms. 218 Coogee Bay Road benefits from a 4.8m* street frontage to Coogee Bay Road, offering pronounced traffic exposure through high amounts of foot traffic due to the extreme proximity to Coogee Beach, just 150m* from the property. 

Coogee Beach is widely recognised as one of Sydney’s most popular beaches and is located only 7km* from Sydney CBD in Sydney’s desired Eastern Suburbs, in turn, attracting global travellers seeking Australia’s enviable beach lifestyle. 218 Coogee Bay Road benefits from its premium position on Coogee’s main thoroughfare, just moments from Coogee Beach, retail amenity, schools, parks, and an assortment of dining options.


218 Coogee Bay Road, Coogee benefits from the following key attributes:

•First time offered to the market in 47 years
•Opportunity to occupy or invest in a trophy location in Coogee
•Situated just 150m* from the popular Coogee Beach
•Rear lane access plus two undercover car spaces 
•Two storey freehold building with basement storage
•High exposure position affording tremendous foot and vehicular traffic to the property
•Highly desirable Eastern suburbs location in proximity to shops, schools, parks, beaches and an expansive variety of dining and recreation options 
•Gross Floor Area: 223.84sqm* (Plus 32.67sqm* external area)
•B2 Local Centre zoning and 12m height limit, allowing for future development potential (STCA)
•Offered with vacant possession

218 Coogee Bay Road, Coogee will be sold via an online Public Auction at auctionWORKS on Tuesday 27 July 2021 at 10:30am (Registration, livestream and online bidding available)

Private inspection appointments will be undertaken.
